01:04.066 --> 01:05.300
you won't feel a thing.

01:07.133 --> 01:11.733
so, tell me, doc. how many
heart transplants have you done?

01:11.799 --> 01:14.666
<i>dos o tres.
[ coughs ]</i>

01:14.733 --> 01:16.466
<i>más o menos.</i>

01:19.633 --> 01:20.833
whoa, whoa, wait.

01:20.900 --> 01:22.432
doc, i-i'm --
i'm not under yet.

01:22.499 --> 01:23.633
i'm still here.

01:23.699 --> 01:25.766
hey, doc, doc, doc,
i'm still here.

01:25.833 --> 01:27.633
i'm still here, doc.

01:27.699 --> 01:30.000
[ speaking spanish ]
i'm still here.

01:30.066 --> 01:32.000
i'm still here!

01:32.066 --> 01:33.166
i'm still here!

01:35.799 --> 01:37.432
it's okay, baby.

01:37.499 --> 01:39.200
it's okay.

01:39.267 --> 01:41.900
it was a dream, right?

01:41.966 --> 01:43.033
it was
just another dream.

01:47.033 --> 01:48.733
he's going.

01:48.799 --> 01:50.499
all right, haley,
i just wanted

01:50.566 --> 01:52.900
to spend this weekend
with my son and my friends.

01:52.966 --> 01:54.267
i barely even know
this guy.

01:54.333 --> 01:55.633
he's going.

01:55.699 --> 01:56.799
you're going.

01:56.866 --> 01:58.699
an entire weekend
in the woods --

01:58.766 --> 02:01.100
you realize i know nothing
about camping?

02:01.166 --> 02:03.333
what does this guy even know
about camping?

02:03.399 --> 02:05.267
he makes movies --
and not very good ones.

02:05.333 --> 02:07.133
julian lives
in tree hill now.

02:07.200 --> 02:09.233
it's time he hung out
with the guys.

02:09.300 --> 02:12.866
i'm not a guy's guy.
i don't have homies.

02:12.933 --> 02:17.166
i don't think anyone
has had homies since 1989.

02:17.233 --> 02:19.166
i'm just saying my close friends
have always been girls.

02:19.233 --> 02:20.599
you mean like alex?

02:20.666 --> 02:23.367
yes, exactly like...

02:23.432 --> 02:25.432
i'm going.

02:26.733 --> 02:28.333
yeah.

02:41.499 --> 02:44.399
hi, clay.

02:44.466 --> 02:46.466
you know how cute
i always thought you were.

03:06.066 --> 03:09.699
oh, i bet you'd like that,
wouldn't you, you perv?

03:09.766 --> 03:11.699
i-i'm sorry.

03:11.766 --> 03:13.799
"fast times" was on cable
last night.

03:13.866 --> 03:16.699
show a little respect
for the dead, you goof.

03:18.200 --> 03:20.966
sara.

03:21.033 --> 03:23.799
this isn't healthy, is it?

03:23.866 --> 03:25.499
oh, i don't know --
probably healthier

03:25.566 --> 03:27.833
than all the women you've had
in your pool in real life.

03:27.900 --> 03:31.733
then again,
skipping the guys' weekend

03:31.799 --> 03:34.000
to spend time
with your dead wife...

03:34.066 --> 03:37.033
probably
not so healthy.

03:53.499 --> 03:56.000
man, when i said
guys' weekend,

03:56.066 --> 03:59.066
i pictured us by the pool
at the bellagio,

03:59.133 --> 04:01.432
room and drinks comped
all 'cause we're rolling
with nathan scott.

04:01.499 --> 04:03.300
yeah, that's exactly
what i wanted --

04:03.367 --> 04:05.166
a weekend
in some casino sports book --

04:05.233 --> 04:07.532
50 tvs, 50 stations,
none of which will hire me.

04:07.599 --> 04:09.333
yeah,
but the damn woods,

04:09.399 --> 04:12.466
with hungry animals
and dudes with hockey masks?

04:12.532 --> 04:14.633
come on, man. camping's a great
way to forget your life.

04:14.699 --> 04:15.933
no tv, no internet,
no cellphones.

04:16.000 --> 04:17.466
yeah.
no way to call for help.

04:19.267 --> 04:21.065
no, i guess
it'll be all right.

04:23.000 --> 04:25.333
hi, coach skills.

04:25.399 --> 04:26.833
aw, chuck.

04:30.267 --> 04:34.033
and above all,
just be yourself.

04:34.100 --> 04:36.799
brooke, it's a camping trip,
not the first day of school.

04:38.367 --> 04:39.799
well, did you remember
to bring

04:39.866 --> 04:41.466
a little thermos
with the sippy cup?

04:41.532 --> 04:43.300
i got it covered.

04:46.532 --> 04:49.866
geez, eddie bauer!
did you buy the whole catalog?

04:49.933 --> 04:53.100
first rule of camping --
be prepared.

04:54.333 --> 04:55.833
i think.

04:57.166 --> 04:59.933
first rule of camping --
travel light.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.633
attention,
all campers.

05:05.666 --> 05:07.466
bill murray?
"meatballs"?

05:07.532 --> 05:09.933
hey, look, everyone.
it's julian.

05:10.000 --> 05:12.264
who the hell is julian?

05:15.066 --> 05:16.933
have a good weekend!
see ya!see ya!

05:17.000 --> 05:18.267
see ya, fellas.

05:18.333 --> 05:20.267
bye, guys.
have fun. be safe.

05:20.333 --> 05:22.066
you think we'll ever
see them again?

05:22.133 --> 05:23.799
oh, i wouldn't worry.

05:23.866 --> 05:26.399
julian has enough equipment
to survive in the woods
for seven years.

05:27.733 --> 05:29.466
well, i hope you're ready
for girls' night,

05:29.532 --> 05:32.599
'cause quinn
made brownies.

05:32.666 --> 05:34.200
brownies!

05:34.267 --> 05:36.300
mmm.
they smell incredible.

05:36.367 --> 05:38.466
they should.
they're taylor's recipe.

05:38.532 --> 05:42.100
oh, sweet.
i love taylor's brownies.

05:43.666 --> 05:45.499
when hales was
in high school,

05:45.566 --> 05:47.566
she used get all stressed
about grades and tests,

05:47.633 --> 05:49.333
and we would always make
special brownies.

05:49.399 --> 05:50.966
special brownies?

05:51.033 --> 05:53.166
yeah, you know,
the usual --

05:53.233 --> 05:56.300
eggs, milk, brownie mix...
a little weed.

05:56.367 --> 05:58.066
does she know that?

05:58.133 --> 05:59.954
no.

06:01.300 --> 06:02.966
looks like the boys
aren't the only ones

06:03.033 --> 06:04.699
going on a trip tonight.

06:35.433 --> 06:38.333
who wants to get their
"go get me a beer" badge?

06:38.400 --> 06:39.733
i do!i do!

06:39.799 --> 06:41.166
nice.

06:43.300 --> 06:46.200
so, this is the same tent
the japanese climbers took

06:46.266 --> 06:48.467
to the top
of mt. everest.

06:48.532 --> 06:50.599
well, then you should
be good here,

06:50.666 --> 06:52.000
100 feet above sea level.

06:52.066 --> 06:55.367
if only the instructions
weren't also in japanese.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.033
well, i think
that looks pretty good.

07:06.100 --> 07:08.966
so, would you call that
a two-man tent?

07:13.200 --> 07:15.799
you might want to slow down
a little.

07:17.267 --> 07:19.408
That was the thing about
Taylor's brownies.

07:19.408 --> 07:20.833
the more i eat,
the hungrier i get.

07:20.866 --> 07:20.899
yeah, there's
a reason for that.

07:22.766 --> 07:27.066
it's girls' night, right --
all about spilling secrets?

07:29.632 --> 07:32.367
oh, no.
what'd you guys do?

07:32.433 --> 07:35.467
okay, taylor's recipe
calls for an eighth

07:35.532 --> 07:37.000
of granddaddy purple.

07:37.066 --> 07:38.733
what is that, some kind
of breakfast cereal?

07:40.499 --> 07:42.733
not exactly.

07:46.000 --> 07:47.400
pot?!

07:49.000 --> 07:50.200
i have to go throw up.

07:50.266 --> 07:51.433
no, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

07:51.499 --> 07:53.467
oh, relax, haley-bob.
you're about to, anyway.

07:53.532 --> 07:54.833
i do not believe,
all those years,

07:54.899 --> 07:56.166
you and tay were
getting me high.

07:56.233 --> 07:59.632
yeah, who knew tutor girl
was actually stoner girl?

07:59.699 --> 08:03.899
we never gave you the
full-strength recipe until now.

08:03.966 --> 08:05.899
i can't do this.
i have a child!

08:05.966 --> 08:07.699
who is away
for the weekend.

08:07.766 --> 08:10.632
you have had
a rough couple of months.

08:10.699 --> 08:14.100
it is perfectly acceptable
to mellow out a little.

08:15.499 --> 08:17.400
i'm so getting you back
for this.

08:17.467 --> 08:20.033
oh, come tomorrow,
you'll be thanking me.

08:20.100 --> 08:22.233
well, maybe i've built up
an immunity to these brownies.

08:22.300 --> 08:24.266
i mean, i've had two already,
and i don't feel anything.

08:32.366 --> 08:34.698
now, when they say they
represent the lollipop guild,

08:34.765 --> 08:36.366
do you think
that's a trade union?

08:36.433 --> 08:38.066
and if it is,
why did they unionize?

08:38.133 --> 08:39.532
did they need
shorter hours

08:39.599 --> 08:41.332
or longer sticks
or different flavors?

08:41.400 --> 08:43.799
look at their little suits.
they really crack me up.

08:45.100 --> 08:47.799
wow.
that didn't take very long.

08:47.866 --> 08:49.833
brooke, are you okay?

08:51.233 --> 08:53.467
will you please tell
that munchkin

08:53.532 --> 08:56.033
to stop looking at me?

08:57.733 --> 09:00.200
great. she gets chatty,
and you get paranoid.

09:14.400 --> 09:16.866
a classic
overcorrection.

09:20.566 --> 09:25.933
just give me something
simple, elegant, beautiful.

09:26.000 --> 09:30.733
you just described
everything i love about you.

09:30.799 --> 09:34.100
i thought you didn't believe
in love.

09:34.166 --> 09:37.699
isn't that what you told
that girl kylie?

09:37.766 --> 09:40.033
i meant...

09:40.100 --> 09:42.866
i could never love anyone
as much as i loved you.

09:42.933 --> 09:44.799
except for quinn.

09:44.866 --> 09:47.966
it's not like that
with quinn.

09:48.033 --> 09:50.566
i could always tell
when you were lying.

09:56.367 --> 09:57.733
the ratings are in.

09:57.799 --> 10:00.966
last week's show with renee
was our highest ever.

10:01.033 --> 10:02.066
i'm glad.

10:02.133 --> 10:03.899
we have momentum.

10:03.966 --> 10:05.632
we need something big
for sweeps,

10:05.699 --> 10:07.200
and then dr. phil
can suck it.

10:07.266 --> 10:09.933
well, maybe we can get lucas
to do a guest spot.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.966
it's not like
he's doing anything.

10:13.266 --> 10:15.766
hey, lena, beat it.
he's got enough eyeliner.

10:18.100 --> 10:19.866
okay.
what's going on?

10:19.933 --> 10:21.766
does this have anything
to do with the fact

10:21.833 --> 10:23.632
that nathan never called
to say thank you?

10:23.699 --> 10:26.899
of course not.
i never expected that.

10:26.966 --> 10:29.833
good, because we both know
that's not gonna happen.

10:29.899 --> 10:32.599
now get your head
in the game.

10:32.666 --> 10:34.300
we have an empire
to build.

10:43.599 --> 10:45.599
alex isn't that bad
once you get to know her.

10:45.666 --> 10:47.666
i'm just saying
i've known brooke a long time.

10:47.733 --> 10:50.233
i saw how hard it was for her
to get over a broken heart.

10:50.300 --> 10:53.300
well, nobody's gonna break
brooke's heart.

10:53.367 --> 10:57.100
well, good, 'cause if you do,
you'll answer to me.

10:57.166 --> 11:00.833
yeah, and i seen him naked.
he been working out.

11:00.899 --> 11:03.000
hanging with the guys
rules.

11:03.066 --> 11:04.367
so, how you doing,
chuck?

11:04.433 --> 11:06.766
my mom says
you can't marry miss lauren

11:06.833 --> 11:09.033
'cause you don't make
enough money.

11:09.100 --> 11:10.766
ah, well,
guess who just lost

11:10.833 --> 11:13.566
their "keep their
damn mouth shut" badge.

11:13.632 --> 11:14.866
so, over the last
few months,

11:14.933 --> 11:16.400
with everything
that's been going on,

11:16.467 --> 11:17.799
maybe you
were kind of scared?

11:17.866 --> 11:18.966
jamie:
not really.

11:19.033 --> 11:22.133
i knew grandpa dan
would save us again.

11:23.966 --> 11:26.733
so, can we
forgive him now?

11:29.632 --> 11:32.166
last week i helped
a confused young woman

11:32.233 --> 11:36.300
free herself from her tangled
web of lies and deceit.

11:40.300 --> 11:43.433
but tonight is about you.

11:43.499 --> 11:46.632
so tonight i ask you
to turn your gaze inward

11:46.699 --> 11:51.367
and confess the truth
inside yourself...

11:51.433 --> 11:54.300
to turn your gaze inward...

11:57.599 --> 12:00.333
...and confess.

12:11.100 --> 12:12.400
and confess --

12:12.467 --> 12:14.367
confess the tru--

12:20.200 --> 12:23.266
we should've saved that
for sweeps.

12:37.500 --> 12:39.533
that was awesome!

12:39.600 --> 12:41.333
one bravery badge
coming right up.

12:41.400 --> 12:44.233
whoa.

12:44.299 --> 12:45.767
it's your turn,
j. luke!

12:48.700 --> 12:50.500
it's so far down.

12:50.566 --> 12:53.066
this was my favorite part
of camping when i was your age.

12:54.833 --> 12:57.066
all right, jimmy-jam.
see what you got.

12:59.566 --> 13:01.767
i can't do it.

13:01.833 --> 13:03.966
[ chuckles ]
what are you talking about?

13:04.032 --> 13:07.166
it's -- it's too high.
i'm going back down the trail.

13:08.833 --> 13:10.433
i better go with julian.

13:10.466 --> 13:10.500
jamie, we've been talking
about this for weeks, man.

13:15.266 --> 13:17.433
but he might get lost.

13:17.500 --> 13:19.066
that's true.
i am directionally challenged.

13:20.833 --> 13:23.566
okay. well, i guess i'll see
you guys at the bottom, then.

13:25.700 --> 13:27.733
whew.
thanks, man.

13:27.800 --> 13:29.266
no problem.

13:31.966 --> 13:33.333
here.

13:36.666 --> 13:38.500
you're a genius,
you know that?

13:38.566 --> 13:39.966
i mean, who could miss
a single episode

13:40.032 --> 13:43.199
when dan scott could keel over
and die at any minute?

13:43.266 --> 13:46.466
i saw something
out there, rachel,

13:46.533 --> 13:47.999
in the audience.

13:50.666 --> 13:54.066
a boy --
he was bleeding.

13:57.032 --> 13:59.833
felt like my heart was
gonna burst out of my chest.

13:59.899 --> 14:01.932
you're crazy.

14:01.999 --> 14:04.500
your heart's fine.

14:06.433 --> 14:09.032
without a new heart,
you're gonna die.

14:09.099 --> 14:11.099
maybe i want to die.

14:14.266 --> 14:16.133
lon called
from putnam and pratt.

14:16.199 --> 14:18.767
he read the first three chapters
of the book.

14:18.833 --> 14:20.899
he says it's gonna be
a bestseller.

14:20.966 --> 14:25.366
think of all the good we'll do,
all the people we'll help.

14:25.433 --> 14:26.899
all the money we'll make?

14:26.966 --> 14:28.999
that too.

14:31.166 --> 14:33.800
how much is this heart
costing us?

14:33.867 --> 14:35.032
$5,000.

14:35.099 --> 14:37.566
that's very reasonable.

14:37.633 --> 14:38.767
it's a fortune
to these people.

14:40.633 --> 14:43.333
now get some sleep.

14:44.733 --> 14:47.433
tomorrow you're gonna be
a new man.

15:01.433 --> 15:04.600
sara, did you feel
any pain...

15:04.666 --> 15:07.466
when you died,
in that moment?

15:07.533 --> 15:09.433
no.

15:09.500 --> 15:11.099
well, i did.

15:12.700 --> 15:15.800
and i do, every day.
and it's not fair.

15:15.867 --> 15:18.833
life isn't fair, clay.

15:18.899 --> 15:24.666
but you being miserable
is never gonna change that.

15:34.366 --> 15:36.867
these leftovers
are incredible.

15:36.932 --> 15:38.533
i am such a good cook.

15:43.299 --> 15:45.932
what's going on with you
and the hot agent?

15:45.999 --> 15:47.199
clay?

15:48.999 --> 15:53.308
who are we talking about?
nathan's agent, clay.

15:53.999 --> 15:55.533
right.

15:55.600 --> 15:57.400
is something going on
with the two of you?

15:57.466 --> 16:01.199
no, but it's better
that way.

16:01.266 --> 16:04.233
my psychic told me to avoid
emotional entanglements.

16:04.299 --> 16:05.633
you have a psychic?

16:05.700 --> 16:08.066
she's not really mine.

16:08.133 --> 16:09.600
her name's zelda.

16:09.666 --> 16:12.066
oh, my god.
she does house calls.

16:12.133 --> 16:14.566
oh, my god.
we are totally calling her.

16:14.633 --> 16:16.366
no.
no, no. no.

16:16.433 --> 16:19.500
please, no creepy psychic --
i can't handle it right now.

16:19.566 --> 16:22.666
see if she can bring us
a pizza.

16:28.366 --> 16:29.932
we did this
in a movie i just produced.

16:29.999 --> 16:31.466
we just need one spark.

16:39.333 --> 16:40.500
all right, spielberg.

16:40.566 --> 16:42.299
why don't you produce us
some marshmallows?

16:45.266 --> 16:48.099
so, the girl say
she thinks she heard a noise

16:48.166 --> 16:49.999
scratching
on the car door, right?

16:50.066 --> 16:51.500
so she freak out.

16:51.566 --> 16:54.366
she tell the dude,
"take me home now."

16:54.433 --> 16:56.899
so of course
he get all mad

16:56.966 --> 16:59.333
because he know he's
not getting no action
tonight, right?

16:59.400 --> 17:00.899
so he drive the girl
all the way home.

17:00.966 --> 17:03.433
and get out the car to try
to help her out, you know?

17:03.500 --> 17:08.031
and there on the door handle
was a bloody hook.

17:08.098 --> 17:09.999
that story isn't scary,

17:10.066 --> 17:12.165
not when you have
a bravery badge.

17:12.233 --> 17:14.532
you want to hear something
really scary?

17:14.599 --> 17:17.098
bring it, julia.

17:17.165 --> 17:19.165
okay.

17:19.233 --> 17:21.532
well, this is a true story
about an old witch

17:21.599 --> 17:23.400
who used to live
in these very woods.

17:25.199 --> 17:28.266
her name
was drag-leg laura.

17:28.333 --> 17:31.299
and they called her that
because she had a wooden leg.

17:31.366 --> 17:33.566
and you could always
hear laura coming

17:33.633 --> 17:37.066
because she would drag it
behind her in the mud.

17:41.700 --> 17:45.433
well, the day
after laura died,

17:45.500 --> 17:48.533
some kids decided that
they wanted to dig up her body

17:48.600 --> 17:50.199
and steal the wooden leg.

17:50.266 --> 17:52.767
so they took it
back to their tent.

17:52.833 --> 17:56.466
and then, just about midnight,
on a night just like tonight,

17:56.533 --> 17:58.233
they heard it.

18:00.099 --> 18:02.867
laura was coming back
for her leg.

18:07.466 --> 18:09.166
wow.
that was fast.

18:09.233 --> 18:10.600
it's because
she's a psychic,

18:10.666 --> 18:12.400
so she probably knew
that we were going to call her

18:12.466 --> 18:13.700
